@HostAddress = http://localhost:5080

### Scenario A1: Null Reference in Order Summary (Application A — Backend Bug)

POST {{HostAddress}}/api/support/emails
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Sender": "dev.team@example.com",
  "Subject": "NullReferenceException in GetOrderSummary endpoint",
  "Body": "We have a critical bug in Application A. The GetOrderSummary endpoint in OrderController.cs throws a NullReferenceException when order.Items is null. Orders created via CreateOrder start with Items = null because items are added later through a separate endpoint. Any call to GetOrderSummary before items are added crashes the API with a null reference on the .Sum() and .Count calls at lines 27-28."
}

### Scenario A2: Incorrect Data Binding in Order Summary Component (Application A — Frontend Bug)

POST {{HostAddress}}/api/support/emails
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Sender": "frontend.dev@example.com",
  "Subject": "OrderSummary.razor displays blank total price",
  "Body": "In Application A, the OrderSummary.razor component binds to Order?.TotalCost, but the OrderSummaryDto model defines the property as TotalPrice. The component renders nothing for the total price field because TotalCost does not exist on the DTO. The fix should change the binding on line 14 from TotalCost to TotalPrice."
}

### Scenario A3: Missing Test for Empty Order Edge Case (Application A — QA/Test Issue)

POST {{HostAddress}}/api/support/emails
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Sender": "qa.lead@example.com",
  "Subject": "Missing test coverage for null/empty Items in OrderServiceTests",
  "Body": "In Application A, the OrderServiceTests class has tests for orders with items but is missing a test for the edge case where an order has no items (Items is null or empty). This gap means the null reference bug in OrderController.GetOrderSummary goes undetected by the test suite. There is only a comment placeholder at lines 35-44 where the missing test should be."
}

### Scenario B1: SQL Injection in User Search (Application B — Backend Bug)

POST {{HostAddress}}/api/support/emails
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Sender": "security.team@example.com",
  "Subject": "SQL Injection vulnerability in SearchUsers endpoint",
  "Body": "We found a critical security vulnerability in Application B. The SearchUsers endpoint in UserController.cs at line 27 concatenates user input directly into a SQL query string without parameterization. An attacker can inject arbitrary SQL such as '; DROP TABLE Users; -- to read, modify, or delete data. The query variable is built using string concatenation instead of parameterized queries."
}

### Scenario B2: Missing Null Check on Avatar URL (Application B — Frontend Bug)

POST {{HostAddress}}/api/support/emails
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Sender": "ui.developer@example.com",
  "Subject": "Broken image rendered when AvatarUrl is null in UserProfile",
  "Body": "In Application B, the UserProfile.razor component renders an img tag with src set to User.AvatarUrl without checking for null at line 11. When AvatarUrl is null, the browser renders a broken image icon and makes a spurious HTTP request to the current page URL. The fix should add a null coalescing fallback to a default avatar image."
}

### Scenario B3: Flaky Test Due to Hardcoded Date (Application B — QA/Test Issue)

POST {{HostAddress}}/api/support/emails
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Sender": "ci.admin@example.com",
  "Subject": "Flaky test CreateUser_WithValidData_SetsCreatedDate fails in CI",
  "Body": "In Application B, the CreateUser_WithValidData_SetsCreatedDate test in UserServiceTests.cs asserts that the user CreatedAt.Date equals new DateTime(2024, 1, 15) at line 18. This hardcoded date was valid only on the day the test was written. The test fails on every other day, making it flaky and unreliable in CI. The fix should compare against DateTime.UtcNow.Date instead."
}

### Edge Case: Out-of-Scope Email (non-code-related request)

POST {{HostAddress}}/api/support/emails
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Sender": "employee@example.com",
  "Subject": "Password reset request",
  "Body": "Hi support, I forgot my password and cannot log into my account. Can you please reset it for me? My username is jsmith. Thanks!"
}

### Edge Case: Ambiguous Routing (mentions both Application A and Application B)

POST {{HostAddress}}/api/support/emails
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Sender": "tech.lead@example.com",
  "Subject": "Data sync issue between Application A and Application B",
  "Body": "We are seeing a data synchronization problem where orders created in Application A are not reflected in the user dashboard of Application B. The OrderController in Application A sends events but the UserController in Application B never receives them. Both applications need to be investigated."
}

### Edge Case: Failed Routing (mentions neither application)

POST {{HostAddress}}/api/support/emails
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Sender": "external.user@example.com",
  "Subject": "Generic API timeout errors",
  "Body": "We are experiencing intermittent timeout errors when calling the API. The requests take over 30 seconds and eventually return a 504 Gateway Timeout. This started happening after the last deployment. No specific application or service is identified."
}

